# Headline files for the predict-rlm comparison benchmarks.
# Only the headline runs cited in the clean reports are committed.
# All other fresh runs (timestamped) land here as untracked work.

# Ignore everything by default
*

# Then re-include the headline files and this .gitignore itself
!.gitignore
!image-analysis_2026-05-20_150618.edn
!image-analysis_2026-05-20_150618.trace.edn
!document-redaction_2026-05-20_165215.edn
!document-redaction_2026-05-20_165215.trace.edn
# PR10 headline output: the actual workbook the model produced (referenced
# from reports/03_invoice_processing.md). Kept as a reference for
# side-by-side comparison with predict-rlm's published invoice_extraction.xlsx
# under references/predict-rlm/invoice_processing/sample/output/.
!invoice_extraction.xlsx
# PR08/PR09 headline output: human-readable artifacts derived from the
# document-redaction headline EDN. Lets reviewers inspect the redacted
# document without re-running the benchmark.
!document_redaction_artifacts/
!document_redaction_artifacts/**
# PR document_analysis headline (referenced from reports/04_document_analysis.md)
!document-analysis-predict-rlm_2026-05-21_162203.edn
